  "prompt": "What are uncurious people like?",
  "response": "Uncurious people tend to have characteristics like:\n\n1. Lack of enthusiasm for learning\n- Disinterested in new information\n- Rarely ask questions\n- Resistant to exploring different perspectives\n\n2. Mental comfort zone\n- Prefer familiar ideas and routines\n- Avoid challenging their existing beliefs\n- Uninterested in personal growth\n\n3. Passive information consumption\n- Accept information without critical thinking\n- Don't seek deeper understanding\n- Satisfied with surface-level knowledge\n\n4. Low intellectual engagement\n- Minimal desire to understand complex topics\n- Limited reading or learning habits\n- Minimal interest in intellectual discussions\n\n5. Narrow worldview\n- Limited exposure to diverse experiences\n- Lack of empathy for different perspectives\n- Tend to be less adaptable\n\n6. Reduced problem-solving skills\n- Less likely to explore creative solutions\n- Rely on established methods\n- Struggle with innovative thinking\n\n7. Lower personal development\n- Less likely to acquire new skills\n- Limited personal and professional growth\n- Less adaptable to changing environments\n\nThese traits can vary in intensity and aren't absolute. People might be curious in some areas and less curious in others.",
